  "text": "In this section, we evaluate the performance of the proposed MHWMA chart by using different run length characteristics such as the average run length and standard deviation of the run length (SDRL) distribution. ARL is the most commonly used performance measures for control chart procedures. The in-control ARL (denoted by ARL 0 ), is the average number of plotted samples until an out-of-control signal is detected by a control chart when the process is in control. The out-ofcontrol ARL (denoted by ARL 1 ), is the average number of plotted points until an out-of-control signal is detected by a control chart when the process is out of control [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] . It is generally desirable to have large values of ARL 0 and small values of ARL 1 for any control-chart setting [CITATION_3] . The SDRL measures the spread of the run length distribution of the ARL [CITATION_4] . Similarly, SDRL 0 and SDRL 1 can be defined.",
